Complete Application Development - Phase Plan
Phase 1: Foundation & Setup (Week 1)
Goal: Project setup and basic infrastructure

Create Android Studio project (Kotlin)
Set up dependencies (Room, Hilt, Coroutines, Navigation)
Design complete database schema (all entities)
Create base architecture (MVVM structure folders)
Set up Hilt dependency injection
Create navigation graph structure
Design color schemes (light + dark theme)
Deliverable: Empty app with structure ready

Phase 2: Authentication System (Week 1)
Goal: User can register and login

Create User entity and DAO
Implement UserRepository
Build Login screen UI
Build Register screen UI
Password encryption with BCrypt
Email validation
Session management with SharedPreferences
Splash screen that checks if user logged in
Deliverable: Working login/register flow

Phase 3: Core Account Management (Week 2)
Goal: Manage bank accounts

Create BankAccount entity and DAO
Build Profile screen UI
Display user information
Add/Edit/Delete bank accounts
Store account name, bank name, balance
Set one account as "Main Account"
Calculate total balance across all accounts
Deliverable: Users can manage their accounts

Phase 4: Basic Transaction System (Week 2-3)
Goal: Add and view transactions

Create Transaction entity and DAO
Build Add Transaction dialog/screen
Input: amount, description, category (dropdown), type (debit/credit)
Account selector for multiple accounts
Implement automatic balance deduction/addition
Create transaction list view (RecyclerView)
Edit and Delete transaction functionality
Transaction detail view
Deliverable: Full CRUD operations on transactions

Phase 5: Dashboard/Home Screen (Week 3)
Goal: Main screen showing overview

Build dashboard layout
Display total balance card
Display recent transactions (last 10)
Show quick stats: total income, total expenses
FAB button for quick "Add Transaction"
Pull-to-refresh functionality
Navigate to other screens
Deliverable: Functional home screen

Phase 6: Budget Management (Week 4)
Goal: Set and track budgets

Create Budget entity and DAO
Build Budget screen UI
Set budget amount and period (Monthly/Yearly)
Track spent amount automatically
Progress bar showing budget usage
Edit/Delete budget
Auto-deduct from budget when transaction added
Budget remaining card on dashboard
Deliverable: Budget tracking works

Phase 7: Notifications System (Week 4)
Goal: Notify users of important events

Set up notification channels
Transaction added notification (shows remaining balance)
Budget alert at 80% usage
Budget exceeded alert at 100%
Notification preferences in settings
Request notification permissions (Android 13+)
Deliverable: Smart notifications working

Phase 8: Search & Filter (Week 5)
Goal: Find transactions easily

Implement search functionality (SearchView)
Search by description, category, amount
Basic filters: date range, category, type
Create filter bottom sheet UI
Advanced filters: amount range, multiple categories
Save filter presets to database
Quick filter chips
Deliverable: Powerful search and filtering

Phase 9: Analytics & Charts (Week 5-6)
Goal: Visual data representation

Integrate MPAndroidChart library
Create pie chart for category-wise spending
Create bar chart for monthly comparison
Create line chart for spending trends
Summary screen with date range picker
Month-end summary report
Category breakdown view
Deliverable: Visual analytics working

Phase 10: Dark Mode & UI Polish (Week 6)
Goal: Better visual experience

Implement dark theme resources
Theme toggle in settings
Create empty state illustrations
Add loading states (shimmer effect)
Screen transitions and animations
Chart animations
Card entry/exit animations
Test all screens in both themes
Deliverable: Polished UI with dark mode

Phase 11: Onboarding & Help (Week 7)
Goal: Guide new users

Create onboarding screens (ViewPager2)
4-5 intro slides with Lottie animations
First-time tutorial flow
Tooltips for complex features
Help section in settings
Re-watchable tutorials
Skip button for returning users
Deliverable: User-friendly onboarding

Phase 12: Recurring Transactions (Week 7)
Goal: Auto-add regular expenses

Create RecurringTransaction entity
Add "Make Recurring" toggle on Add Transaction
Set frequency (daily, weekly, monthly, yearly)
WorkManager setup for auto-adding
Daily check for due recurring transactions
Notification when auto-added
Pause/Resume/Delete recurring transactions
View all recurring transactions list
Deliverable: Recurring transactions automated

Phase 13: Smart Insights (Week 8)
Goal: AI-powered spending insights

Query and compare month-over-month data
Generate insights (30% more spent on Food)
Unused subscription detection
Spending pattern predictions
Display insights cards on dashboard
Insight detail view with charts
Budget adherence score calculation
Deliverable: Smart insights showing

Phase 14: Export & Reports (Week 8)
Goal: Generate and share reports

Implement CSV export (transaction data)
Implement Excel export (Apache POI)
Generate PDF reports (iText library)
Date range selection for exports
Share receipt images for transactions
Email report functionality
Save to device storage
Deliverable: Export and sharing works

Phase 15: ML Auto-Categorization (Week 9)
Goal: Smart category suggestions

Create training dataset (descriptions â†’ categories)
Integrate TensorFlow Lite
Train text classification model
Implement on-device prediction
Show category suggestions when adding transaction
User feedback to improve model
Fallback keyword-based categorization
Deliverable: Smart category suggestions

Phase 16: Goals/Savings (Week 9)
Goal: Track savings goals

Create SavingsGoal entity
Build Goals screen UI
Add/Edit/Delete goals
Set target amount and deadline
Manual contribution to goals
Progress tracking with visual indicators
Goal achievement celebration
Link transactions to goals
Deliverable: Savings goal tracking

Phase 17: Receipt Management (Week 10)
Goal: Attach and scan receipts

Add photo storage for transactions
Camera integration (Intent or CameraX)
Gallery picker
Store photos in app storage
Integrate ML Kit Text Recognition
OCR to extract amounts from receipts
Receipt gallery view
Delete/replace receipt photos
Deliverable: Receipt management complete

Phase 18: Bill Splitting (Week 10)
Goal: Split expenses with friends

Create SplitTransaction and SplitParticipant entities
"Split Bill" option after transaction
Add participants (manual or contacts)
Equal or custom split amounts
Track payment status
Payment reminders
Share payment request via WhatsApp/SMS
Settlement summary
Deliverable: Bill splitting functional

Phase 19: Calendar View (Week 11)
Goal: Calendar-based transaction view

Integrate MaterialCalendarView library
Display transactions on calendar dates
Color-coded dots for transaction days
Tap date to view transactions
Month/Week view toggle
Filter calendar by category
Add future planned expenses
Swipe navigation between months
Deliverable: Calendar view working

Phase 20: Advanced Features (Week 11-12)
Goal: Performance and extras

Database indexing optimization
Implement Paging 3 for transaction lists
RecyclerView optimizations (DiffUtil)
Dashboard data caching
WorkManager for heavy calculations
Settings screen (preferences)
Biometric authentication option
App backup/restore functionality
About screen with version info
Deliverable: Optimized and feature-complete

Phase 21: Testing & Bug Fixes (Week 12-13)
Goal: Quality assurance

Unit tests for ViewModels
Unit tests for Repositories
Database tests
UI tests for critical flows
Test edge cases (zero balance, negative amounts)
Test on different screen sizes
Test on different Android versions (API 24-34)
Fix bugs and crashes
Memory leak checks
Deliverable: Stable, tested app

Phase 22: Final Polish & Launch Prep (Week 13-14)
Goal: Production ready

App icon design
Splash screen polish
Performance profiling
Error handling improvements
Privacy policy creation
App store screenshots
App store description
Play Store listing setup
Generate signed APK/AAB
Beta testing with users
Deliverable: Production-ready app